47:15.532 --> 47:18.035
(eerie music)

47:21.839 --> 47:24.508
(phone ringing)

47:26.009 --> 47:27.511
- The mayor is here to see you.

47:31.882 --> 47:32.716
- Send him in.

47:37.721 --> 47:39.590
- Morbid, terrible shame.

47:40.724 --> 47:42.326
He's a good man.

47:42.359 --> 47:43.994
Gonna be hard to replace.

47:43.994 --> 47:44.828
- Thanks for coming.

47:44.862 --> 47:45.696
Have a seat.

47:50.434 --> 47:51.602
- Where'd you get that?

47:53.070 --> 47:54.238
- Deputy brought it in.

47:55.505 --> 47:57.841
He didn't know what else to do with it.

47:57.875 --> 48:00.210
- The lake is 31 miles long.

48:02.512 --> 48:03.513
- I understand that.

48:04.581 --> 48:06.416
If you allow me to call the harbor patrol.

48:06.450 --> 48:09.019
- No harbor patrol.

48:09.052 --> 48:10.520
Too much negative attention.

48:12.589 --> 48:15.392
You know, anybody can take the wheel of a ship

48:15.392 --> 48:19.263
in calm waters, but the waves get rough, not so easy.

48:20.697 --> 48:22.266
We can't just sit back and enjoy the good times.

48:22.266 --> 48:24.234
We've gotta stand tough through it all.

48:25.769 --> 48:27.604
- I appreciate the pep talk, but sir.

48:28.939 --> 48:30.974
- Not a pep talk, warden. That is a promise.

48:33.410 --> 48:36.980
This town has not seen a murder in more than half a century.

48:38.715 --> 48:41.118
A shark in these waters? That's unheard of.

48:42.286 --> 48:43.487
Sheriff Wilson's dead.

48:44.955 --> 48:47.224
I can deal with that end of the mess,

48:47.224 --> 48:50.494
but you gotta get a handle on this disaster

48:50.494 --> 48:52.296
and live up to your end of the deal.

48:54.231 --> 48:55.732
- Deal?

48:55.732 --> 48:58.568
- Do your fucking job so I can save mine.

48:59.903 --> 49:01.071
I need to know what you're gonna do

49:01.104 --> 49:02.973
about this shark problem.

49:05.275 --> 49:06.643
- I got a charter coming in.

49:08.111 --> 49:10.280
I asked Wilson to shut down the lake, but he refused.

49:12.015 --> 49:15.585
- We can shut down the lake without shutting down the lake.

49:15.619 --> 49:17.988
I'll have my office put out a statement.

49:17.988 --> 49:19.823
Work being performed on the dam.

49:21.491 --> 49:23.493
Sheriff Wilson's another story,

49:25.295 --> 49:27.631
but the coroner's exam is gonna take a couple of days,

49:27.664 --> 49:29.166
maybe enough time for us to come up

49:29.166 --> 49:31.368
with some sort of response.

49:33.103 --> 49:34.271
- There is no response.

49:35.205 --> 49:36.873
We got two people dead.

49:36.940 --> 49:39.943
Now the two options I see is that we cut off

49:39.977 --> 49:43.480
the shark's food supply or wait it out,

49:43.480 --> 49:45.949
and see if it starves itself to death.

49:45.949 --> 49:47.384
That's it.

49:47.384 --> 49:50.220
- And you are the authority on this?

49:50.220 --> 49:52.389
- I spoke to the experts.

49:52.456 --> 49:54.224
I drove down to the Ocean Institute.

49:59.463 --> 50:02.065
- This town can survive anything on two feet.

50:02.065 --> 50:04.634
Wild cats, sharks.

50:04.668 --> 50:06.169
There's only one person around here

50:06.169 --> 50:08.238
who's gonna take the fall for that sort of thing.

50:10.073 --> 50:11.641
Always nice to see you, Reema.

50:18.382 --> 50:22.219
(dramatic, suspenseful music)

50:29.593 --> 50:32.329
(motor whirring)

50:35.332 --> 50:38.335
(suspenseful music)

51:19.443 --> 51:22.212
(Spencer grunts)

51:23.980 --> 51:26.316
(liquid splashing)

51:26.383 --> 51:27.818
(tense music)

51:27.818 --> 51:30.487
- See if you're hungry now, you son of a bitch.

51:30.487 --> 51:33.156
(phone buzzing)

51:35.926 --> 51:36.760
Yeah?

51:39.463 --> 51:40.931
Yeah, no, I know.

51:40.964 --> 51:42.065
I just didn't look at the damn calendar is all.

51:43.800 --> 51:45.836
Yeah, no, that's fine.

51:45.902 --> 51:48.238
It's work. What do you want me to do?

51:50.607 --> 51:52.843
No, we're not done talking about the paper signing.

51:52.843 --> 51:55.912
(tense music)

51:55.946 --> 51:57.114
No, I gotta go.

52:01.485 --> 52:04.020
(gun blasting)

52:10.327 --> 52:12.829
(tense music)

52:19.836 --> 52:21.304
(engine revving)

52:21.304 --> 52:23.773
(water warbling)

52:23.773 --> 52:26.510
(motor whirring)

52:36.153 --> 52:38.855
(truck rumbling)

52:43.193 --> 52:44.027
Already?

52:44.961 --> 52:46.029
- Yes, already.

52:46.029 --> 52:47.564
You forget, didn't you?

52:47.631 --> 52:48.565
- No, I just thought it was gonna be

52:48.565 --> 52:50.066
later in the day, that's all.

52:50.133 --> 52:52.969
Hey, what I'd tell you about bringing the gun in the house?

52:53.003 --> 52:53.837
- I'm sorry, Dad.

52:53.837 --> 52:55.172
- It's all right.

52:55.205 --> 52:57.174
Apologies won't get you anywhere faster.

52:58.842 --> 52:59.643
- Yes, sir.

53:03.980 --> 53:05.182
- Hey, listen.

53:05.215 --> 53:06.716
I will be back to pick you up Sunday.

53:06.716 --> 53:09.186
You call me if you need anything, okay?

53:12.222 --> 53:14.090
Well, have a good weekend.

53:14.157 --> 53:14.991
- Yeah.

53:20.764 --> 53:23.533
(engine revving)

53:25.835 --> 53:27.204
- She's still mad, huh?

53:27.237 --> 53:28.071
- Yeah, you're screwed.

53:28.071 --> 53:29.239
- Yeah, I thought so.

53:32.342 --> 53:34.211
You keeping it clean like I showed you?

53:34.244 --> 53:35.078
- Yeah.

53:36.179 --> 53:37.581
- Good.

53:37.581 --> 53:39.849
Responsibility, it'll teach you

53:39.883 --> 53:41.384
how to do things for yourself.

53:44.221 --> 53:46.089
- There's no TV in the guest room.

53:47.924 --> 53:49.292
- Oh yeah, about that, yeah.

53:50.560 --> 53:51.394
Take my room.

53:52.562 --> 53:54.064
I gotta work this weekend anyway.

53:55.265 --> 53:56.233
Hey, don't pout.

53:57.434 --> 53:58.935
We'll call up Uncle Gary, come over here

53:58.969 --> 54:00.370
and keep you company until I get back.

54:00.403 --> 54:03.106
- I'm 13. I don't need a babysitter.

54:03.106 --> 54:04.941
Besides, he's not even a real uncle.

54:04.941 --> 54:06.943
He's just some guy from your AA meetings.

54:07.877 --> 54:08.712
Seriously?

54:10.113 --> 54:11.114
- I deserve that.

54:13.783 --> 54:15.585
But I need you to stay by the house.

54:19.055 --> 54:21.057
- Mom said you were working on the lake?

54:22.325 --> 54:23.727
- Yeah, it's nothing.

54:23.760 --> 54:25.629
We're just looking for something, but it reminds me.

54:25.629 --> 54:28.465
You stay out of the water this weekend, too.

54:28.465 --> 54:30.100
I don't want you down there with your buddies,

54:30.133 --> 54:31.835
flirting with girls, all right?

54:31.835 --> 54:33.503
Stay outta the water.

54:33.503 --> 54:34.671
Hey, I need to hear you say it.

54:34.671 --> 54:35.672
- I'll stay out of the lake.

54:35.739 --> 54:36.673
- [Spencer] Stay out of the lake.

54:36.673 --> 54:37.841
You promise? - Promise.

54:37.841 --> 54:39.309
- All right, you promised me.

54:45.615 --> 54:46.483
You hungry?

54:46.483 --> 54:47.317
- I can eat.

54:50.654 --> 54:52.088
- We might have to order out.

54:52.088 --> 54:53.523
But let's see. - That's fine.

54:53.523 --> 54:55.091
Your cooking sucks anyways.

54:55.125 --> 54:56.693
- [Spencer] Yeah, I know.

54:56.693 --> 54:59.429
(water splashing)

54:59.462 --> 55:02.365
(crickets chirping)

55:08.938 --> 55:11.641
(water warbling)

55:14.277 --> 55:15.679
(crickets chirping)

55:15.679 --> 55:18.214
(gentle music)

55:22.452 --> 55:25.822
(water splashing gently)

55:29.025 --> 55:32.028
(crickets chirping)

55:43.340 --> 55:46.242
(engine whirring)

