1:03:15.491 --> 1:03:18.995
(phone continues buzzing)

1:03:24.467 --> 1:03:25.968
Grant!

1:03:25.968 --> 1:03:27.136
Oh, fuck, boy.

1:03:28.504 --> 1:03:29.338
Grant!

1:03:34.277 --> 1:03:35.111
Grant!

1:03:36.012 --> 1:03:37.346
Goddamn it, son.

1:03:39.148 --> 1:03:39.982
Grant!

1:03:41.384 --> 1:03:42.718
Goddamn it, son.

1:03:44.520 --> 1:03:45.555
Shit.

1:03:45.555 --> 1:03:48.057
(tense music)

1:03:55.198 --> 1:03:57.133
(water splashing)

1:03:57.133 --> 1:03:58.301
Grant!

1:03:58.301 --> 1:03:59.569
Get outta the water!

1:03:59.569 --> 1:04:00.803
Grant!

1:04:00.837 --> 1:04:01.671
Grant!

1:04:01.704 --> 1:04:03.706
Get outta the water.

1:04:03.706 --> 1:04:06.142
- What? - Get outta the water.

1:04:07.510 --> 1:04:08.845
Oh my God. Shit.

1:04:10.079 --> 1:04:13.583
(tense, suspenseful music)

1:04:13.583 --> 1:04:16.018
(Grant gurgling)

1:04:16.052 --> 1:04:18.888
(water splashing)

1:04:23.726 --> 1:04:24.560
Grant.

1:04:26.762 --> 1:04:27.897
Get on my back, son.

1:04:27.897 --> 1:04:29.098
Listen to me.

1:04:29.165 --> 1:04:30.833
Listen to me, there's a shark in the lake.

1:04:30.867 --> 1:04:32.201
I need you to get on my back

1:04:32.201 --> 1:04:33.703
and hang on till we get to shore.

1:04:33.736 --> 1:04:36.439
Right. (grunts)

1:04:36.439 --> 1:04:38.074
(tense music)

1:04:38.074 --> 1:04:40.243
Don't look back, son.

1:04:40.243 --> 1:04:41.077
Ah!

1:04:45.781 --> 1:04:47.683
Come on, come on.

1:04:47.717 --> 1:04:48.718
It's okay.

1:04:48.751 --> 1:04:49.585
Come on.

1:04:49.585 --> 1:04:50.753
Gotta move, boy.

1:04:50.753 --> 1:04:53.723
(Grant yells) (water splashing)

1:04:53.756 --> 1:04:55.258
We're almost there. (Grant yells)

1:04:55.258 --> 1:04:56.092
We're almost there.

1:04:56.092 --> 1:04:57.093
We're almost there.

1:04:57.093 --> 1:04:58.294
Lay down, buddy.

1:04:58.294 --> 1:05:00.396
Yeah, you're all right.

1:05:00.429 --> 1:05:01.230
Hey, look at me.

1:05:01.230 --> 1:05:02.064
Stay with with me.

1:05:02.064 --> 1:05:05.234
Oh. (Grant yells)

1:05:05.268 --> 1:05:06.903
Hey, hey, listen to me.

1:05:06.903 --> 1:05:08.070
I gotta move you.

1:05:08.070 --> 1:05:09.305
I gotta get you patched up, all right?

1:05:09.305 --> 1:05:10.640
You gotta be brave for me, all right?

1:05:10.640 --> 1:05:11.707
Grab hold of my neck.

1:05:11.741 --> 1:05:12.775
Grab hold of my neck, you ready?

1:05:12.775 --> 1:05:16.312
One, two, three. (Grant screams)

1:05:16.379 --> 1:05:19.215
(water splashing)

1:05:46.275 --> 1:05:48.477
(door shuts)

1:05:48.477 --> 1:05:50.479
- What in the hell were you thinking?

1:05:52.748 --> 1:05:54.250
Spencer.

1:05:54.250 --> 1:05:55.584
- Stitches, all right?

1:05:55.618 --> 1:05:57.153
He's gonna be fine. - I'm not talking about that.

1:05:57.153 --> 1:05:58.354
The whole ride over here,

1:05:58.421 --> 1:06:00.423
he's telling me he was attacked by a shark.

1:06:00.456 --> 1:06:01.257
Is that true?

1:06:03.759 --> 1:06:05.928
Oh my God. And you didn't tell me?

1:06:07.129 --> 1:06:08.631
- Would it have done any good? No.

1:06:08.664 --> 1:06:10.166
- I wouldn't have brought him here if I knew that.

1:06:10.166 --> 1:06:11.701
You know he loves the water.

1:06:11.767 --> 1:06:14.136
- Hey, I told him, stay outta the lake, okay?

1:06:15.171 --> 1:06:16.105
He lied to me too.

1:06:16.105 --> 1:06:19.141
- Okay, I can stay here tonight.

1:06:19.175 --> 1:06:20.343
I'll drive him home in the morning.

1:06:20.343 --> 1:06:22.011
But Spencer, what the hell is going on?

1:06:24.714 --> 1:06:26.215
- There's a shark in the lake.

1:06:27.383 --> 1:06:30.486
Don't ask me how, but it survived.

1:06:30.519 --> 1:06:32.021
It's killed three people.

1:06:32.021 --> 1:06:33.990
- And this isn't on the news?

1:06:36.058 --> 1:06:38.394
And somehow you're in charge of this?

1:06:39.662 --> 1:06:42.131
- They need a fall guy. You're looking at him.

1:06:43.899 --> 1:06:45.701
- Spencer, I know you.

1:06:45.701 --> 1:06:48.537
Whatever this is, you cannot serve two masters.

1:06:50.039 --> 1:06:52.041
- I'm clean.

1:06:52.074 --> 1:06:55.378
On our son, I am clean.

1:06:55.378 --> 1:06:57.380
- What are you gonna do?

1:06:59.348 --> 1:07:01.984
- Mayor doesn't want me to bring attention to it,

1:07:01.984 --> 1:07:03.686
can't hire a guy to kill the shark.

1:07:05.388 --> 1:07:06.555
It's gotta be me.

1:07:06.555 --> 1:07:07.823
- Spencer, they're just looking for an out

1:07:07.857 --> 1:07:09.859
when this thing blows up in their faces.

1:07:09.892 --> 1:07:12.395
(tense music)

1:07:13.496 --> 1:07:14.430
What?

1:07:14.430 --> 1:07:16.265
- What'd you just say?

1:07:16.265 --> 1:07:18.734
I said, they're gonna blame you for this.

1:07:18.734 --> 1:07:19.769
- No, no, after that.

1:07:20.936 --> 1:07:22.405
It'll blow up in their faces.

1:07:24.740 --> 1:07:25.708
- I can help.

1:07:27.576 --> 1:07:29.111
(gun cocks)

1:07:29.178 --> 1:07:30.079
- Let's go.

1:07:32.048 --> 1:07:32.882
Nolan Holt.

1:07:34.784 --> 1:07:36.719
Get your ass out here.

1:07:36.752 --> 1:07:37.887
- Oh, hell.

1:07:39.588 --> 1:07:43.092
What'd you come all the way over here to arrest my ass?

1:07:43.092 --> 1:07:44.760
- No, I came to help you.

1:07:44.794 --> 1:07:46.262
- Help me?

1:07:46.262 --> 1:07:47.096
- Yeah.

1:07:49.298 --> 1:07:50.099
- Who's she?

1:07:52.401 --> 1:07:53.936
- [Spencer] It's my wife.

1:07:53.936 --> 1:07:57.039
- Ex-wife. - Nothing's been signed yet.

1:07:58.908 --> 1:08:00.576
- So you two need to get on the same page.

1:08:00.576 --> 1:08:01.544
- Nevermind all that, Nolan.

1:08:01.544 --> 1:08:02.978
It's not why I'm here.

1:08:02.978 --> 1:08:04.814
I'm here because I need you as much as you need me.

1:08:04.880 --> 1:08:05.948
All right?

1:08:05.948 --> 1:08:06.782
- Oh yeah?

1:08:07.917 --> 1:08:09.151
What do you want from me?

1:08:09.151 --> 1:08:11.587
- You wanna make this shark thing disappear?

1:08:11.620 --> 1:08:14.056
Save your sorry ass in the process?

1:08:14.056 --> 1:08:15.591
I need you to do something for me.

1:08:17.626 --> 1:08:19.228
- All right, what do you want?

1:08:19.228 --> 1:08:21.063
- Do you have anything that explodes?

1:08:22.298 --> 1:08:25.134
Now think, dynamite, gunpowder, anything.

1:08:25.134 --> 1:08:26.936
- C-4.

1:08:26.969 --> 1:08:27.803
- What?

1:08:29.004 --> 1:08:30.272
- What?

1:08:30.306 --> 1:08:31.140
- C-4.

1:08:32.308 --> 1:08:33.476
You want something that explodes, right?

1:08:33.476 --> 1:08:35.945
Well, that's the ticket right there.

1:08:35.978 --> 1:08:37.146
What you want it for?

1:08:37.146 --> 1:08:38.347
- Where in the hell did you get C-4?

1:08:38.414 --> 1:08:40.483
- What, we gonna ask 20 questions here?

1:08:40.483 --> 1:08:41.984
Or do you want the damn stuff?

1:08:44.019 --> 1:08:45.321
- What do you want for it?

1:08:49.592 --> 1:08:51.127
- Get the sheriff off my ass.

1:08:53.863 --> 1:08:54.697
- Deal.

1:08:59.368 --> 1:09:00.169
Thanks, Nolan.

1:09:06.008 --> 1:09:08.878
- Be sure you poke it with a stick.

1:09:10.779 --> 1:09:12.681
(Nolan imitates explosion)

1:09:12.681 --> 1:09:15.351
Right, Macho Man? (chuckles)

1:09:17.153 --> 1:09:19.655
(tense music)

1:09:37.239 --> 1:09:39.008
- Here, take over up front.

1:09:39.041 --> 1:09:41.577
Anything breaks the surface, you shoot it.

1:09:41.577 --> 1:09:44.079
(tense music)

1:09:59.428 --> 1:10:01.931
If he's in the shallow waters,

1:10:03.098 --> 1:10:05.401
all I gotta get him to do now is swallow this.

1:10:06.435 --> 1:10:08.671
- Okay, then what?

1:10:08.704 --> 1:10:11.207
- Then we blow it to pieces with this.

1:10:18.614 --> 1:10:20.115
(liquid splashes)

1:10:20.182 --> 1:10:23.285
(Spencer gags)

1:10:23.285 --> 1:10:24.220
- All right.

1:10:24.253 --> 1:10:25.221
- That should get his attention.

1:10:25.221 --> 1:10:26.055
- Now what?

1:10:26.956 --> 1:10:27.790
- Now?

1:10:29.024 --> 1:10:30.192
Now we wait.

1:10:30.192 --> 1:10:33.195
(suspenseful music)

1:10:35.130 --> 1:10:37.066
(birds chirping)

1:10:37.099 --> 1:10:39.935
(water splashing)

1:10:45.140 --> 1:10:45.941
I don't get it.

1:10:47.443 --> 1:10:49.078
Damn thing should've been here by now.

1:10:50.946 --> 1:10:52.214
I'm almost out of bait.

1:10:52.214 --> 1:10:54.283
- Maybe we should move to a different spot.

1:10:55.884 --> 1:11:00.756
- Deeper waters won't work, in case one of us has to get in.

1:11:01.390 --> 1:11:02.658
- Get in?

1:11:02.658 --> 1:11:05.661
As in get in the water with the shark?

1:11:05.728 --> 1:11:07.229
- How else do you expect it to swallow the C-4?

1:11:07.263 --> 1:11:08.764
- I don't know.

1:11:08.764 --> 1:11:10.065
I thought it would come close enough we could just toss it

1:11:10.065 --> 1:11:11.300
in its mouth.

1:11:11.300 --> 1:11:13.469
- Really? Yeah, that'd be easier, for sure.

1:11:17.139 --> 1:11:20.109
- You're not seriously considering this, are you?

1:11:20.109 --> 1:11:21.577
- Oh, what? What's this?

1:11:21.577 --> 1:11:23.078
Huh?

1:11:23.078 --> 1:11:24.513
All of a sudden, you give a shit about what happens to me?

1:11:24.513 --> 1:11:26.348
I needed this person before, not now.

1:11:27.182 --> 1:11:28.017
- So did I.

1:11:29.852 --> 1:11:31.153
(Spencer stumbles)

1:11:31.153 --> 1:11:32.488
- Fuck.

1:11:32.521 --> 1:11:34.189
This ain't working.

1:11:34.256 --> 1:11:35.457
I'm getting in.

1:11:37.826 --> 1:11:42.331
(Dottie breathing shaking) (metallic rattling)

1:11:42.364 --> 1:11:44.133
- Just make it a clean shot. - No!

1:11:45.367 --> 1:11:48.437
(water splashes)

1:11:48.470 --> 1:11:50.806
(tense music)

1:11:50.839 --> 1:11:55.110
(suspenseful adventure music)

1:11:55.110 --> 1:11:57.212
Come on, come on, come on, come on.

1:11:57.212 --> 1:11:59.682
(tense music)

1:12:00.716 --> 1:12:01.984
- Come on.

1:12:02.017 --> 1:12:04.019
Oh, come on, oh come on.

1:12:04.019 --> 1:12:06.522
(tense music)

1:12:07.856 --> 1:12:10.526
(Dottie grunts)

1:12:12.194 --> 1:12:14.963
(water bubbling)

1:12:18.000 --> 1:12:19.201
Shoot it!

1:12:19.201 --> 1:12:22.037
(gunshot blasting) (C-4 exploding)

1:12:22.037 --> 1:12:24.740
(Dottie panting)

1:12:29.545 --> 1:12:32.247
(birds chirping)

1:12:35.818 --> 1:12:38.487
(both grunting)

1:12:40.389 --> 1:12:45.394
- Come here. (Dottie panting)

1:12:46.228 --> 1:12:49.264
We did it. (Dottie gasping)

1:12:49.331 --> 1:12:51.867
(both panting)

1:12:53.869 --> 1:12:56.205
(birds chirping)

1:12:56.238 --> 1:12:58.941
(phones ringing)

1:13:05.080 --> 1:13:06.749
- I'm glad you're starting over.

1:13:06.749 --> 1:13:08.350
All of you.

1:13:08.384 --> 1:13:10.586
Gonna miss you around here, Warden.

1:13:10.586 --> 1:13:12.354
- Nah, the new guy'll do just fine.

1:13:13.756 --> 1:13:16.258
Besides, quitting while you're still good at something

1:13:16.258 --> 1:13:17.593
ain't the same as quitting.

1:13:19.094 --> 1:13:21.430
- I can't seem to find that thermos of yours anywhere.

1:13:22.297 --> 1:13:23.198
- No, it's gone.

1:13:24.366 --> 1:13:25.534
I don't need it anymore.

1:13:27.102 --> 1:13:29.471
- Well, if you ever wanna stop and pay a visit,

1:13:29.471 --> 1:13:32.775
there will always be a pot of coffee on for you.

1:13:32.775 --> 1:13:33.609
- I believe it.

1:13:36.145 --> 1:13:37.479
Thanks, Reema.

1:13:37.479 --> 1:13:40.215
(phones ringing)

1:13:49.792 --> 1:13:52.394
(box rustling)

1:13:53.796 --> 1:13:58.500
(water splashing) (birds chirping)

1:13:58.567 --> 1:14:00.903
(seagulls cawing)

1:14:00.936 --> 1:14:03.405
(tense music)

1:14:05.407 --> 1:14:08.110
(dramatic music)

1:14:09.244 --> 1:14:12.815
(tense, suspenseful music)

1:14:33.502 --> 1:14:35.804
- Yeah, I'm working on my book right now, Bubba.

1:14:37.139 --> 1:14:39.942
Well, it ain't finished yet.

1:14:39.942 --> 1:14:41.810
I mean, I'm working on it as we speak.

1:14:43.045 --> 1:14:46.148
Yeah, it'll be out soon. (chuckles)

1:14:46.181 --> 1:14:47.349
First I'm gonna go out on the lake,

1:14:47.349 --> 1:14:49.051
I'm gonna get me some dinner.

1:14:49.051 --> 1:14:50.886
Get me some of that poontang fish fin,

1:14:50.886 --> 1:14:52.888
you know what I mean?

1:14:52.955 --> 1:14:56.625
Shark fin, if I can. (chuckles)

1:14:56.658 --> 1:14:58.193
All right, I'll call you back.

1:14:58.193 --> 1:14:59.361
All right, all right, all right.

1:14:59.394 --> 1:15:02.731
(leaves crunching)

1:15:02.798 --> 1:15:03.632
Whoo!

1:15:05.167 --> 1:15:08.003
(water splashing)

1:15:08.871 --> 1:15:10.405
Goddamn, it's cold.

1:15:11.874 --> 1:15:12.708
Whoo!

1:15:14.910 --> 1:15:15.744
Whoo-whee.

1:15:17.713 --> 1:15:18.547
Yeah.

1:15:24.686 --> 1:15:26.855
I'll get you tonight, boy.

1:15:30.359 --> 1:15:34.530
Oh, yeah. (hums)

1:15:42.538 --> 1:15:43.372
All right.

1:15:51.580 --> 1:15:55.083
(line thwacking) Oh yeah!

1:15:55.083 --> 1:15:58.086
(Nolan grunts)

1:15:58.086 --> 1:16:03.025
There we go. (water splashing)

1:16:12.200 --> 1:16:13.035
Chapter 1.

1:16:15.070 --> 1:16:16.905
"Terror in the Water."

1:16:18.874 --> 1:16:21.777
Today's October 3rd, 2021.

1:16:24.780 --> 1:16:27.583
It's been three weeks since this sleepy town

1:16:27.583 --> 1:16:29.084
been ravaged by...

1:16:31.620 --> 1:16:32.454
The lake shark.

1:16:37.292 --> 1:16:38.894
Ah.

1:16:38.894 --> 1:16:43.165
It's been three weeks since this town...

1:16:45.767 --> 1:16:48.604
Been ravaged the silent predator known

1:16:48.604 --> 1:16:50.772
as the lake monster.

1:16:52.441 --> 1:16:55.277
(water splashing)

1:16:59.281 --> 1:17:02.818
It's been three weeks since this sleepy town

1:17:04.453 --> 1:17:07.856
been ravaged the Lone Star Shark.

1:17:10.492 --> 1:17:14.262
Yeah! Got a best-seller, you know it, boy.

1:17:14.262 --> 1:17:15.631
Whoo! Good stuff.

1:17:16.832 --> 1:17:18.333
Oh, ooh, ooh, ooh.

1:17:19.201 --> 1:17:20.035
Oh boy.

1:17:21.003 --> 1:17:23.205
Goddamn it, son of a bitch!

1:17:25.674 --> 1:17:28.777
Dumb piece of shit. (grunts)

1:17:28.777 --> 1:17:30.946
Am I stuck on something? What is that?

1:17:30.946 --> 1:17:34.716
Goddamn it. (water splashing)

1:17:34.716 --> 1:17:39.721
Where's it at? (tense music)

1:17:40.822 --> 1:17:45.727
Oh, shit! (water splashing)

1:17:47.329 --> 1:17:49.698
This is Nolan Holt, confirming the worst fears:

1:17:50.799 --> 1:17:52.300
the Lone Star Shark lives on.

1:17:53.735 --> 1:17:55.303
Stay tuned.

1:17:55.337 --> 1:17:58.173
(water splashing)

1:18:03.245 --> 1:18:06.682
(Nolan breathes shakily)

1:18:11.987 --> 1:18:15.157
(Nolan screams)

1:18:15.157 --> 1:18:18.694
(tense, suspenseful music)

1:19:20.055 --> 1:19:23.892
(dramatic, suspenseful music)

1:19:53.955 --> 1:19:56.691
(dramatic music)
